         <abstract id="aspace_949296e222ace6c50a9786bf339b0719">Correspondence and account books relating to Reed's activities in Batavia, Netherlands East Indies, as a representative of Paine, Stricker  Company of Amsterdam, a trading company. Correspondents include his wife, Caroline Suzette van Son Reed (1825-1861); the Band, Cramerus, Hasselman, van Alphen, and van Braam families, to which he was related by marriage; and Cramerus  Company, Amsterdam. Includes material relating to service and charitable projects in which Reed participated.</abstract>
